<article class="post single-post-content">

		 
	 <h1 class="post-title">Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham</h1>

	<div class="post-meta">
	
		<em>by</em> Emily Bites		<em>on</em> April 27, 2026		<span class="spacer"></span>
		<span class="ccount"><a href="https://emilybites.com/2026/04/creamy-tomato-pasta-with-ham.html#comments">1 comment</a></span>
			
		<div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-custom-snippet"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="35629" style="color: #2e4162;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal">Jump to Recipe</a>
</div>
	</div>
		
	<div class="post-content">
		<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-35626" src="https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-5b-728x1092.jpg" alt="Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham in the pan" width="728" height="1092" data-pin-description="This Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham is a family-friendly meal that’s perfect for weeknights and just 328 calories or 9 WW Points per 1 &amp; 1/4 cups serving!" data-pin-title="Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham" srcset="https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-5b-728x1092.jpg 728w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-5b-364x546.jpg 364w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-5b-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-5b.jpg 1456w" sizes="(max-width: 728px) 100vw, 728px" /></p>
<p>This Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham is a flavorful, family-friendly dinner that’s perfect for a weeknight meal! I adapted and lightened up this recipe from NYT Cooking originally called <a href="https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1023157-penne-al-baffo-creamy-tomato-ham-pasta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Penne al Baffo</a>, which has rave reviews. With a rich, creamy tomato sauce, salty ham, hearty mushrooms, and nutty Parmesan cheese, this lightened up version still tastes decadent and delicious! Plus, you’ll love that this recipe is easy to make without a lot of prep work or ingredients. Each filling 1 &amp; ¼ cup serving of this Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham is just 328 calories or 9 WW Points on Weight Watchers! <em>To view your current WW Points for this recipe and track it in the WW app, <a href="https://cmx.weightwatchers.com/details/MEMBERRECIPE:69e6efc5e5f2d69c59da4c1a?shared=true" target="_blank" rel="noopener">click here</a>!</em><span id="more-35625"></span></p>
<h3><strong>Recipe Notes</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pasta:</strong> Any medium-sized pasta types work well in this recipe, such as penne, fusilli, orecchiette, farfalle, cavatappi, or shells. Use what you like or have on hand!</li>
<li><strong>Ham:</strong> I used pre-cubed ham in this because it’s super convenient and already comes chopped and ready to go! I generally find it in 8 ounce packages by the packaged deli meat or bacon in my local stores. I’ve bought Hormel and Smithfield brands and both work great! The original recipe I adapted this from used sliced deli ham, chopped, up, so you can definitely use that instead if you have some on hand or prefer thinly sliced ham pieces.</li>
<li><strong>Tomato Passata/Puree:</strong> The most common brand I see for this is Mutti, though Wegmans (my local grocery chain) also has a store brand version. It typically comes in glass bottles rather than cans in my experience. Passata is just smoothly pureed uncooked tomatoes and is a bit thicker, whereas canned tomato sauce is often pre-cooked and seasoned with salt and spices. I really like the passata/puree in this recipe, but if you have trouble finding it or already have canned tomato sauce on hand, feel free to use the canned!</li>
<li><strong>Mushrooms:</strong> I used pre-sliced Baby Bella mushrooms in this recipe which was super easy and delicious, though sliced white mushrooms would also work just fine.</li>
<li><strong>Alternative Vegetables:</strong> Not a mushroom fan? No problem! You can omit them if you like, but I enjoy having a veggie included. I think zucchini, summer squash, or spinach would all work well as a replacement. If you decide to use spinach you can just wait and stir it in at the end of the sauce simmer, before adding the cheese and half-and-half.</li>
<li><strong>Serving Suggestion:</strong> I think this Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham pairs really well with a side salad with either Italian dressing or Balsamic vinaigrette!</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-35627" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20728%20910'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham in a bowl" width="728" height="910" data-pin-description="This Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham is a family-friendly meal that’s perfect for weeknights and just 328 calories or 9 WW Points per 1 &amp; 1/4 cups serving!" data-pin-title="Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham" data-lazy-srcset="https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-728x910.jpg 728w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-364x455.jpg 364w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-768x960.jpg 768w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b.jpg 1456w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 728px) 100vw, 728px" data-lazy-src="https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-728x910.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-35627" src="https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-728x910.jpg" alt="Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham in a bowl" width="728" height="910" data-pin-description="This Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham is a family-friendly meal that’s perfect for weeknights and just 328 calories or 9 WW Points per 1 &amp; 1/4 cups serving!" data-pin-title="Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham" srcset="https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-728x910.jpg 728w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-364x455.jpg 364w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b-768x960.jpg 768w, https://emilybites.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Creamy-Tomato-Pasta-with-Ham-7b.jpg 1456w" sizes="(max-width: 728px) 100vw, 728px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><strong>More Tasty Lightened Up Pasta Recipes</strong></h3>
<p>If you love lightened-up pasta recipes like this Creamy Tomato Pasta with Ham and want more options, I’ve got you covered! Check out my <a href="https://emilybites.com/2024/01/one-pot-beefy-creamy-tomato-pasta.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Beefy Creamy Tomato Pasta</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2025/11/cajun-chicken-orzo-skillet.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cajun Chicken Orzo Skillet</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2024/02/one-pot-taco-pasta.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Taco Pasta</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2023/04/one-pot-chicken-parmesan-pasta.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Chicken Parmesan Pasta</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2024/10/easy-skillet-lasagna.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Easy Skillet Lasagna</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2023/02/one-pot-cheeseburger-pasta.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Cheeseburger Pasta</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2023/09/loaded-spaghetti-bake.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Loaded Spaghetti Bake</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2020/02/one-pot-cheesy-chili-mac.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Cheesy Chili Mac</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2020/01/one-pot-turkey-and-veggie-spaghetti.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Turkey and Veggie Spaghetti</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2017/10/chicken-pot-pasta.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chicken Pot Pasta</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2020/03/one-pot-creamy-tomato-pasta-with-chicken-and-spinach.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One-Pot Creamy Tomato Pasta with Chicken and Spinach</a>, <a href="https://emilybites.com/2017/03/lemon-chicken-orzo-with-tomatoes-and-asparagus.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lemon Chicken Orzo</a>, and so many more in the <a href="https://emilybites.com/category/pasta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pasta section of my recipe index</a>!</p>
<div id="recipe"></div><div id="wprm-recipe-container-35629" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="35629" data-servings="8"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-purr-custom"><div class="wprm-recipe-head">

<div class="wprm-image-block">
